Hashtag Popularity Prediction

📌 Project Overview

This project analyzes Twitter data to predict hashtag popularity using Machine Learning (XGBoost, Random Forest). It also includes bot detection, sentiment analysis, and network analysis to understand Twitter trends better.

🚀 Features

Hashtag Popularity Prediction using XGBoost

Feature Engineering: Text complexity, engagement, and time-based features

Bot Detection using followers-to-friends ratio

Sentiment Analysis of tweets

Network Analysis: Finding influential users & hashtag co-occurrence

Optimized Machine Learning Model with hyperparameter tuning

📂 Project Structure

├── twitter.ipynb  
├── tweets_data.csv        ---> Original dataset        
├── processed_tweets.csv   ---> Updated dataset
├── potential_bot_account.csv      
├── requirements.txt       
├── README.md               

🔧 Installation & Setup

Clone this repository:

git clone https://github.com/AliNaraqi/Hashtag-Popularity-Prediction.git
cd Hashtag-Popularity-Prediction

Install dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt

Run the Jupyter Notebook:

jupyter notebook twitter.ipynb

🏆 Model Performance

Optimized Accuracy: Achieved 93% using XGBoost

Hyperparameter tuning via RandomizedSearchCV

Feature importance analysis using SHAP

💡 Future Improvements

Deploying as a web app using Flask/Django

Real-time hashtag trend analysis

Expanding dataset for better accuracy

